&lt;p&gt;At Shakepay, we’re on a mission to usher in the Bitcoin golden age. We’re reimagining financial services to give every Canadian their fair shake.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our culture is built around doing work that matters, winning as a team, and celebrating success. If you&#39;re the kind of person who values growth, shipping fast, and sharing your ideas openly with a group of like-minded people, come and build with us!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About Shakepay&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since 2015, we&#39;ve been on a mission to help Canadians build long-term wealth through bitcoin. Over the past few years, we&#39;ve expanded beyond buying and selling bitcoin to offer a growing suite of everyday financial products - including the Shakepay Card, direct deposit, bill payments and Interac e-Transfer - making it easier to earn, save and use bitcoin every day. Today, more than 1.5 million Canadians use Shakepay to grow their bitcoin savings and take control of their financial future as we continue to push the boundaries of what modern financial services can look like.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re regulated as an investment dealer across all Canadian provinces and territories, and backed by renowned venture capitalists with a funding of $44M. We have a passionate, loyal, and growing community, and we’re looking for people who want to help us build something truly special.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the team&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Legal team sits at the center of some of Shakepay’s most important decisions. We partner closely with Product, Compliance, Operations, Finance, People, and leadership to bring new products to market, navigate complex regulatory questions and help the business move quickly with confidence. We believe ownership over hierarchy, practical judgment over perfection, and using technology and AI to rethink how legal work gets done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Senior Legal Counsel, you’ll help shape how millions of Canadians interact with money. You’ll work alongside product, compliance and executive leadership to solve novel legal questions at the intersection of crypto, payments and financial regulation. This is a hands-on role for someone who can navigate ambiguity, provide practical recommendations and wants to help build - not just protect - the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll be doing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product, Compliance and business teams to help design and launch new products, translating complex legal and regulatory requirements into practical solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on a broad range of legal and regulatory matters across securities, AML/ATF, payments, consumer protection and other areas impacting Shakepay&#39;s business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead regulatory initiatives, including supporting examinations, audits, licensing work, policy development and engagement with regulators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide practical, business-oriented advice to leaders across the company, helping teams navigate ambiguity and make informed decisions while balancing legal, regulatory and operational considerations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to leverage AI, automation and scalable processes to improve how legal work gets done and enable the business to move faster.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team on a variety of other legal matters as needed, including commercial agreements, corporate governance, employment and strategic projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
